The paper focuses on video-based person re-identification, which is a task related to computer vision and image processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a fully convolutional temporal attention model, which involves deep learning techniques, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another likely category. The paper also involves the use of attention mechanisms, which is a popular topic in machine learning and deep learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of sequence labeling, which is a common technique in natural language processing, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible category. Finally, the paper involves the use of benchmark datasets and performance evaluation, which is a common topic in information retrieval, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible category.
